-3%5C%22%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20South%20Africa%20told%20the%20top%20UN%20court%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20aerial%20and%20ground%20offensive%20%E2%80%93%20which%20killed%20almost%2024%2C000%20people%2C%20according%20to%20Gaza%20health%20authorities%20%E2%80%93%20aimed%20to%20bring%20about%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20destruction%20of%20the%20population%E2%80%9D%20of%20Gaza%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-4%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20Israel%20rejected%20these%20accusations%2C%20saying%20it%20respected%20international%20law%20and%20had%20a%20right%20to%20defend%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2Fliveblog%2F2024%2F1%2F12%2Flive-israels-response-to-south-africas-genocide-case-at-the-icj%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Galit%20Raguan%2C%20acting%20director%20of%20the%20international%20justice%20division%20at%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Justice%20Ministry%2C%20blamed%20Hamas%20for%20the%20high%20civilian%20toll%20in%20Gaza%20and%20said%20that%20Israel%20had%20not%20bombed%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20appalling%20suffering%20of%20civilians%2C%20both%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%2C%20is%20first%20and%20foremost%20the%20result%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20strategy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reuters%20reported%20Tal%20Becker%2C%20the%20Israeli%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20legal%20adviser%2C%20as%20saying%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGilad%20Noam%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20attorney%20general%20for%20international%20affairs%2C%20argued%20against%20the%20use%20of%20provisional%20measures%2C%20citing%20reasons%20such%20as%20Hamas%20being%20designated%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20Israel%20and%20other%20countries.%20As%20per%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20also%20pointed%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20a%20large-scale%20terrorist%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Staker%2C%20an%20international%20lawyer%20previou